# =============================================================================
# Hosted Supabase (project ref vdiuezxnlsbxwrdhmmsw)
# =============================================================================
# API URL + publishable/anon keys: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#
# SUPABASE_URL=https://vdiuezxnlsbxwrdhmmsw.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=   # legacy anon JWT or publishable key — browser/client only; RLS must protect data
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=   # server-side only (bypasses RLS). Never expose in frontend bundles or VITE_/NEXT_PUBLIC_
#
# Postgres — direct session mode (port 5432, host db.<ref>.supabase.co).
# Good for long-lived Bun server + scripts. Add ?sslmode=require if your client needs it explicitly.
# For Vercel/serverless, prefer the transaction pooler (port 6543) — see plan.md.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.vdiuezxnlsbxwrdhmmsw.supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
#
# Production / Vercel: set the same secrets in the host’s env store. Never commit passwords or service_role.
# See plan.md for Vercel env var matrix and preview vs production projects.
#
# Hosted DB workflow (from this repo):
#   1. bun run supabase:link          # once; links CLI to the project + DB password
#   2. bun run supabase:migration:list
#   3. bun run supabase:db:push:dry-run && bun run supabase:db:push
#   4. Optional catalog load: bun run upload:cocktails:supabase  (needs DATABASE_URL as above)
#
# Troubleshooting: if `supabase db query --linked` fails with cli_login SASL auth, re-run
# `supabase link` (you will be prompted for the database password) or run SQL in the dashboard.

# =============================================================================
# Local Supabase (Docker — not managed by the Cursor Supabase MCP plugin)
# =============================================================================
# 1. Install & start Docker Desktop.
# 2. `bun run supabase:start` (first run downloads images).
# 3. Print env lines to paste into `.env`:
#    `bun run supabase:local-env`
#    (Uses `supabase status -o env` with names matching SUPABASE_* / DATABASE_URL.)
#
# Or set manually (ports from supabase/config.toml):
# SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<copy from `bun run supabase:status` — Authentication Keys>
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:54322/postgres
#
# Optional: `bun run supabase:db:reset` applies migrations + seed after start.
